				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: First DN fight<a name="65906"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 7 04 10:18 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Tried it with 15 elemental geared players the other night, Main Tank 11k, 1900ac warrior. Pretty much since there weren't any spoilers out there we just walked in and set up shop at the far side of the Hsagra's Shade as mentioned by someone in another thread.  
<br />
Page 15 of the big epic thread I think has the sketchy (imo awesome drawing thank you for it) drawing and the camp site works.
<br />
Here's my small raid, just guildies I had left over from killing an Enchanter epic mob in siren's grotto. Figured we give it a shot or at least figure it out.
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://personal.nbnet.nb.ca/bmac/pics/raid.jpg">
<br />

<br />
Didn't have a clue what the expect, all I knew was 3 zombies and the Vasthan guy will pop a bit away from Hsagra and you have to deal with them 4 while 9 things guard a door.
<br />

<br />
Here's how we setup. Kill off all the ratmen.
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://personal.nbnet.nb.ca/bmac/pics/raid2.jpg">
<br />

<br />
Easy enough get your groups setup here, and you go hand in your bones to Hsagra's Shade. Run back around to the raid you'll see the mobs have all popped.
<br />

<br />
Here's what it looks like from somewheres between the raid and Hsagra's shade looking at the zombies that have popped. This was after I got rezzed up (after the raid was over and all that). Notice we didn't actually kill the zombies. I'm sure we all know a few pulling tricks by now.
<br />
<img src="http://personal.nbnet.nb.ca/bmac/pics/hsagrashade.jpg">
<br />

<br />
Anyways we pulled Vesthan from the blue spot(blue X) over to the raid(green spot), he hits for 800, doesn't do anything special, he might have flurried as a human I can't quite remember if he did or not. He's easy like this but has quite a bit of hp.
<br />

<br />
The real kicker comes when he hits 20% he turns from Vesthan into Vesthan's Abomination, a big dragon construct model with the small hitbox. Anywas it hits pretty hard highest was 1325 or so, it's pretty important to try and get this guy slowed quickly if you have a small raid like we did. He AE rampages, flurries, kept us cramped into a small area and ate us up pretty bad with the AE rampage. We walked him along that back wall a bit.
<br />

<br />
We got him down to 10% before we just ran out of steam, went oom as the healers we're stressed to the max. My healer brought his a-game kept a full group healed and the main tank, how he did it with all of us eating AE rampage in that tight area I don't know, really was doing an amazing job keeping us all alive, since he was both the cleric and the druid in that first group. 
<br />

<br />
Sloppy, very much so, we didn't know what we we're getting into and we tried to minimize the AE rampage ovcourse after we figured it out but we only had a small area to play with didn't want to risk the zombies so often times we we're eating it with the space and the walking along the wall.
<br />

<br />
Pretty sure we won't have any problems next time, I'd feel confident bringing out the same 15 and we could pull it off now that we know what we are doing and what to expect. Elemental rings is about the most we have done so far and mini's, no gods yet. So by no means are we uberly equiped. 
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps us all get the first encounter done and struggle with the next. Sorry I couldn't help with the zombies we just didn't bother with em. We had planned on rooting 1 and offtanking the other 2, but the pull ended up going good for us<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Ghailin Starblaze
65 Maestro
Poison Arrow</span></td>
